**where —** CA · CELLULAR AUTOMATA (CELLULAR AUTOMATA)  Framework inputs: the rule; the grid; the emergence  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)

**why —** Three numbers and a grid: a dead cell with exactly three live neighbors is born; a live cell survives only with two or three. From that alone comes the whole zoo — the most famous cellular automaton ever written.

**how —** Crystallized from the mathematics and computer science of cellular automata and artificial life.

**◌ the mythos —** Three numbers and a grid: a dead cell with exactly three live neighbors is born; a live cell survives only with two or three. From that alone comes the whole zoo — the most famous cellular automaton ever written. a rule, a pattern, or a pioneer of the field

